snippet: A magnitude 7.5 earthquake struck off the coast of Papua New Guinea’s New Britain Province on Tuesday, but early reports said the quake caused only minor damage to buildings.
abstract: Papua New Guinea is struck with fourth significant earthquake in week; no injuries are reported.
lead_paragraph: A magnitude 7.5 earthquake struck off the coast of Papua New Guinea’s New Britain Province on Tuesday, but early reports said the quake caused only minor damage to buildings.

headline.print_headline: Asia; Papua New Guinea: Fourth Earthquake
